org.chronos.chronodb.api.query

Interface NumberCondition

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Condition
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    NegatedNumberCondition
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    EqualsCondition, GreaterThanCondition, GreaterThanOrEqualToCondition, LessThanCondition, LessThanOrEqualToCondition, NotEqualsCondition

    public interface NumberCondition
extends Condition
    A NumberCondition is a Condition on numeric (i.e. int, long, float, double...) values.

    This class comes with two different apply methods, one for longs and one for doubles.

      • negate

        NumberCondition negate()
        Description copied from interface: Condition
        Returns the negated form of this condition.

        This also works for already negated conditions. The following statement is always true: 

         condition.getNegated().getNegated() == condition // always true
        Specified by:
        negate in interface Condition
        Returns:
        The negated condition. For already negated conditions, the regular non-negated condition will be returned.
